Of course! Let's create the workspace on the Desktop:

---

### **STEP 1 — Create SDV workspace on Desktop**
```bash
mkdir -p ~/Desktop/SDV_workspace/{src,models,data,config,scripts,logs,maps}
echo "✅ SDV Workspace created on Desktop!"
ls ~/Desktop/SDV_workspace/
```

---

### **STEP 2 — Update bashrc to point to new location**
```bash
sed -i 's|export SDV_WS=/home/nvidia/SDV_workspace|export SDV_WS=/home/nvidia/Desktop/SDV_workspace|g' ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
echo "SDV workspace is now at: $SDV_WS"
```

---

### **STEP 3 — Set max performance**
```bash
sudo nvpmodel -m 0 && sudo jetson_clocks
echo "✅ MAX PERFORMANCE ON 🚀"
```

---

### **STEP 4 — Now find launch files and check sensors**
```bash
find ~/ros2 ~/Documents/Quanser -name "*.launch.py" 2>/dev/null | sort
```

```bash
source ~/.bashrc
ros2 pkg executables qcar2_nodes
ros2 pkg executables qcar2_autonomy
```

---

📋 Paste outputs and we immediately start building! Now your entire SDV project will be visible and accessible right on the Desktop — clean and organized. 🔥
